# Delta9 Development Rules

## Project Context

Delta9 is an OpenCode plugin implementing Commander + Council + Operators architecture.
Read `docs/spec.md` for full specification. Read `CLAUDE.md` for quick context.

## Code Style

- TypeScript strict mode required
- Zod for all runtime validation
- No `any` type - use `unknown` with type guards
- Functional patterns preferred over classes (except MissionState)
- Export types from `src/types/`

## File Organization

- One component/function per file when possible
- Index files for re-exports
- Max 300 lines per file
- kebab-case for filenames

## Naming Conventions

- `camelCase` for functions and variables
- `PascalCase` for types, interfaces, classes
- `SCREAMING_SNAKE` for constants
- `kebab-case` for files

## OpenCode Plugin Patterns

- Use `@opencode-ai/plugin` types
- Define agents with proper mode (primary/subagent)
- Use `tool()` helper for custom tools
- Register hooks in plugin entry point

## Mission State

- Never mutate `mission.json` directly
- Use `MissionState` class methods
- Validate all state changes with Zod
- Mission state is source of truth

## Agent Boundaries

- Commander: Plans only, never writes code
- Operators: Execute tasks, focused scope
- Validator: Verify against acceptance criteria
- Support agents: Invoked as needed

## Testing

- Framework: Vitest
- New features require tests
- Use `client.app.log()` for debugging

## Don'ts

- Don't use `any` type
- Don't mutate state directly
- Don't skip the Validator gate
- Don't hardcode model names
- Don't let Commander write code
- Don't add features not in spec.md
